purchaseWithEther(uint256).details: Purchase the provide token in EtherReverts if token not unsold and not available to be purchased msg.sender will become the owner of the token msg.value needs to be >= to the token priceInWei

purchaseWithFiat(uint256).details: Purchase the provide token in FIAT, management command only for taking fiat payments during KODA physical exhibitions Equivalent to taking the KODA token off the market and marking as soldReverts if token not unsold and not available to be purchased and not called by management

reverseFiatPurchase(uint256).details: Reverse a fiat purchase made by calling purchaseWithFiat()Reverts if token not purchased with fiat and not available to be purchased and not called by management

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a given token ID to another addressIf the target address is a contract, it must implement `onERC721Received`, which is called upon a safe transfer, and return the magic value `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,uint256,bytes)"))`; otherwise, the transfer is reverted.Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator

params._to: address to receive the ownership of the given token ID
params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be transferred

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a given token ID to another addressIf the target address is a contract, it must implement `onERC721Received`, which is called upon a safe transfer, and return the magic value `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,uint256,bytes)"))`; otherwise, the transfer is reverted.Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator

params._to: address to receive the ownership of the given token ID
